The paper discusses the development of a controller for autonomous vehicles to perform rear end collision avoidance. This involves the use of fuzzy logic and agent-based modeling, which are commonly used in the fields of robotics (cs.RO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of emotion generation mechanisms, which can be related to the field of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the paper discusses the practical validation of the proposed model, which can be related to the field of systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the comparison of the proposed model with existing research, which can be related to the field of machine learning (cs.LG).
